Spain implements control over public expenditure . The Spanish cabinet approved a measure on Friday aimed at strengthening public spending controls , government spokesman Migel Angel Rodriguez said . " The government approved a deal which strengthens expenditure controls . This is a development of the general budget law , " Rodriguez told reporters after the cabinet ' s weekly meeting . Rodriguez added that new controls would be directed especially to public contracts . " It ' s very important . . . because we are talking about more than 70 percent of public expenditure , " he said . - - Madrid newsroom + 34 1 585 8340 
